Class VectorQuery

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.jeo.vector.VectorQuery

      • fields

        public Set<String> fields()
        Set of Feature properties to query, an empty set means all properties.

      • bounds

        public Bounds bounds()
        Bounds constraints on the query, may be null meaning no bounds constraint.

        The bounds constraint applies to VectorDataset.read(VectorQuery) and VectorDataset.update(VectorQuery) operations.

      • filter

        public Filter<Feature> filter()
        Constraint on the query, may be null meaning no constraint.

        The filter constraint applies to VectorDataset.read(VectorQuery) and VectorDataset.update(VectorQuery) operations.

      • limit

        public Integer limit()
        Limit on the number of features to return from the query, null meaning no limit.

        The feature limit applies to VectorDataset.read(VectorQuery) and VectorDataset.update(VectorQuery) operations.

      • offset

        public Integer offset()
        Offset into query result set from which to start returning features, null meaning no offset.

        The feature offset applies to VectorDataset.read(VectorQuery) and VectorDataset.update(VectorQuery) operations.

      • reproject

        public Pair<org.osgeo.proj4j.CoordinateReferenceSystem,org.osgeo.proj4j.CoordinateReferenceSystem> reproject()
        Coordinate reference systems to reproject feature results between, null meaning no reprojection should occur.

        The first element in the pair may be null to signify that the dataset crs (if available) should be used

        The reproject field applies to VectorDataset.read(VectorQuery) and VectorDataset.update(VectorQuery) operations.

      • simplify

        public Double simplify()
        Simplification tolerance to apply to feature geometries, null meaning no simplification.

        The simplification tolerance applies to VectorDataset.read(VectorQuery) and VectorDataset.update(VectorQuery) operations.

      • transaction

        public Transaction transaction()
        Transaction of the query, may be null.

        The transaction applies to VectorDataset.update(VectorQuery) and VectorDataset.append(VectorQuery) operations.

      • adjustCount

        public long adjustCount(long count)
        Adjusts a raw count based on limit and offset of the query.

        The adjusted count is equivalent to: 

         min(max(0, count-offset), limit)

        Returns:
        The adjusted count.

      • missingProperties

        public Set<String> missingProperties(Schema schema)
        Compute missing properties based on the provided schema and the current filter. This allows a format to defer to CQL filtering instead of using native (SQL for example) encoding that may result in errors or invalid results.
        Parameters:
        schema - non-null schema to evaluate the filter against
        Returns:
        non-null Set of any missing properties
